
--- Visuals ---

Not in order:
1. Ambient occlusion
2. Soft shadows (PCF and then softer-when-further-away)
3. Bloom/Emission
https://youtu.be/7oLgEV9ih1M?si=6A8cXluaIsObvbRt

Bloom:
Ideally: Bloom as a post processing effect based on luminance
Bloom also as a seperate voluntary pass so that some meshes can appear to be transmissive/glowing even if they aren't above the luminance threshold

Requires, a seperate pass which uses buffer swapping to progressively blur the image, number of swaps, as well as other bloom params should be configurable.


--- Features ----

- Projection mapping, e.g. casting complex shadows (via video as a projection onto the scene)
